This section describes the common functionalities of Doxee Platform 3 services, excluding EI-EO services.

> Note

For more information on the common functionalities of the Activities, Analytics, Documents, and Invoices services of the Electronic Invoicing and Electronic Ordering Doxee Platform services, see: [Doxee Platform 3 Common Functionalities - EI-EO Services](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-3-common-functionalities-ei-eo-services).

#### Filtering data
The **Search **field at the top allows to search all fields of the elements displayed in the table.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Note

In the **Jobs **service's UI, it is also possible to filters data by specific columns. For more information, see [Search filters](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-3-common-functionalities#search-filters) below.

#### Search filters
- Click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) in the **Search **field to expand the filter options. For example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select the table column for which to set a search filter. For example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select the column value to filter by from the list of available options. For example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- (optional) Repeat steps 13 to add as many filters as needed.

- Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) to start a search using the configured filters, or press **ENTER**.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

The configured filters are displayed at the top of the table. For example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

> Tip

Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) next to a column filter to remove it, or  ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Clear all**) to remove all filters.

> Note

This functionality is only available in the [Batch Jobs](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-batch-jobs-user-manual) and [On-Demand Jobs](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-on-demand-jobs-user-manual) views.

#### Configuring table columns
- Click  ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) on the toolbar at the top. The **Configure Table **panel appears:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) to remove a column, or click ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Add**) to add a column to the table.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- (optional) Drag the selected columns to the desired position using the icon ![](data:image/png;base64,) .

- Click **Configure **to save. The selected columns are now visible in the results table.

> Note

This functionality is only available in the [Batch Jobs](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-batch-jobs-user-manual) and [On-Demand Jobs](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-on-demand-jobs-user-manual) views.

#### Reloading data
Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Refresh**) to reload the data displayed in the table.

#### Viewing the details of an element
To view the details of a table element, select the corresponding checkbox and click ![](data:image/png;base64,). For example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

> Tip

To hide the details panel, click ![](data:image/png;base64,) in the top-right corner or click ![](data:image/png;base64,) again.

> Note

The **Details **panel displays different types of information depending on the selected element.

Every information which has been configured during the release and deploy of a resource will be displayed in the Details panel.
